Clifford George Lacey (1 April 1921 - 16 February 1997) was an Anglican priest: he was the Archdeacon of Lewisham from 1985 to 1989. During the Second World War Lacey served with the RAFVR. He was educated at King's College London [1] and ordained in 1950 and served curacies at Crofton Park and Kingston upon Thames. [2]He held incumbencies at in Merton, Eltham and was the Borough Dean [3] of Greenwich from 1979 to 1985.
